# Cursor cold-start alignment (K-HARDEN-8)

**Start here:** read `AGENTS.md` — the canonical cross-agent contract. It
defines the full read order (§2), risk classes (§5), restricted surfaces (§6),
the PR-only workflow (§14a), the audit doctrine (§9), the obligation ledger
(§16), and the Karpathy coding principles (§13). This file does not restate
those rules.

Cursor obeys that one contract identically to every other platform, and is free
to use its own native strengths — this `.mdc` rule format, `globs`,
`alwaysApply` — to realize it. That is the Layer 1 / Layer 2 model in
`AGENTS.md` §2.

If any rule here contradicts `AGENTS.md`, **`AGENTS.md` wins**. This file exists
because Cursor's auto-discovery prefers `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`.
